cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SE. 

The paper describes a method for semantically marking up LaTeX lecture notes and exposing them as Linked Data, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the use of ontologies to answer queries from students and lecturers suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the application of the method to lecture notes suggests a potential application in software engineering (cs.SE) for educational purposes.
